# deploy

Docker and deployment configuration for `{{ .Name }}`.

- `Dockerfile` — multi-stage build producing a minimal production image
- `docker-compose.yml` — local development stack with all selected services

## Starting the local stack

```bash
# From the project root:
cp .env.example .env          # fill in credentials
docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.yml up -d
```

Docker Compose automatically loads `.env` from the directory where you run the command, resolving all `${VAR}` references in the compose file.

## Stopping

```bash
docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.yml down
# To also remove volumes (wipes all data):
docker compose -f deploy/docker-compose.yml down -v
```
